
Overview of noun margin

The noun margin has 6 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (6) margin, border, perimeter -- (the boundary line or the area immediately inside the boundary)
2. (2) margin -- (an amount beyond the minimum necessary; "the margin of victory")
3. margin, security deposit -- (the amount of collateral a customer deposits with a broker when borrowing from the broker to buy securities)
4. gross profit, gross profit margin, margin -- ((finance) the net sales minus the cost of goods and services sold)
5. margin -- (the blank space that surrounds the text on a page; "he jotted a note in the margin")
6. allowance, leeway, margin, tolerance -- (a permissible difference; allowing some freedom to move within limits)
